In {{yearlink|1360}}, [[Nartheling]], an ancient [[fang dragon]], moved into the mountain.{{cite book/The Grand History of the Realms|145}}

As of {{yearlink|1372}}, the [[Cult of the Dragon]] regularly scaled the mountain to seduce Nartheling with the tranformation into a [[dracolich]].{{cite book/Unapproachable East|106}} The [[copper dragon]] [[Filauxerimos]] preferred to instead avoid the location.{{cite book/Unapproachable East|174}} Nartheling himself was known to raid nearby caravans.

In {{yearlink|1373}}, Nartherling, while succumbing to the rage, got into a number of skirmishes with the beholders, which spilled into the surrounding area.
